<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 13:07:24 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>英国国王的尸骨被移动了几个世纪，最终丢失了。一位研究人员声称他发现了它们的位置——在停车场下面</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-kings-bones-were-moved-over-centuries-and-eventually-lost-one-researcher-claims-he-discovered-their-location-under-a-parking-lot-180989121/</link><description>阿尔弗雷德大帝保卫威塞克斯免受维京人的侵害。在修道院的安息地被扰乱后，研究人员多年来一直在寻找他的遗骸</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 20:37:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-kings-bones-were-moved-over-centuries-and-eventually-lost-one-researcher-claims-he-discovered-their-location-under-a-parking-lot-180989121/</guid></item><item><title>这些可爱的老鼠是如何在没有其他哺乳动物居住的极高海拔地区生活的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-how-these-adorable-mice-can-live-at-an-extremely-high-elevation-where-no-other-mammal-is-known-to-survive-180989116/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，安第斯叶耳鼠具有适应能力，可以帮助其在海拔 22,000 英尺的寒冷、低氧条件下有效地产生体温</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:45:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-how-these-adorable-mice-can-live-at-an-extremely-high-elevation-where-no-other-mammal-is-known-to-survive-180989116/</guid></item><item><title>这座拥有 700 年历史的英国教堂差点关闭，但随后牧师在祭坛下发现了藏匿的金币</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-700-year-old-english-church-nearly-closed-but-then-the-vicar-discovered-a-stash-of-gold-coins-under-the-altar-180989120/</link><description>复活节前夕，一盒 20 世纪 90 年代铸造的金条改变了一小群正在努力支付昂贵维修费用的会众的前景</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:26:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-700-year-old-english-church-nearly-closed-but-then-the-vicar-discovered-a-stash-of-gold-coins-under-the-altar-180989120/</guid></item><item><title>罗马混凝土是如何延续千年的？拥有 1,900 年历史的厕所提供了有关该材料令人印象深刻的耐用性的新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-has-roman-concrete-lasted-for-millennia-a-1900-year-old-latrine-offers-new-clues-about-the-materials-impressive-durability-180989115/</link><description>一种称为碳化的化学过程有助于密封裂缝，这有助于解释为什么许多古罗马建筑至今仍屹立不倒。研究人员希望这些见解能够带来更好的现代建筑材料</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 15:54:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-has-roman-concrete-lasted-for-millennia-a-1900-year-old-latrine-offers-new-clues-about-the-materials-impressive-durability-180989115/</guid></item><item><title>认识最早的已知“右手”动物，一种生活在大约 5.5 亿年前的类似蠕虫的生物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-the-first-right-handed-animal-a-worm-like-creature-that-lived-about-550-million-years-ago-180989107/</link><description>化石分析表明，在埃迪卡拉时期，这种生物在现在南澳大利亚的海底蠕动，并且更喜欢右转</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-the-first-right-handed-animal-a-worm-like-creature-that-lived-about-550-million-years-ago-180989107/</guid></item><item><title>古罗马人相信守护神。考古学家刚刚在英格兰北部发现了一个具有 1,600 年历史的罕见雕刻</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/romans-put-their-faith-in-guardian-spirits-archaeologists-just-found-a-rare-1600-year-old-carving-of-one-in-northern-england-180989118/</link><description>被称为“天才”的保护神或神灵被认为能为特定的人、家庭或地方带来好运和繁荣。考古学家在罗马时期的不列颠并没有发现很多关于他们的描述</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 11:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/romans-put-their-faith-in-guardian-spirits-archaeologists-just-found-a-rare-1600-year-old-carving-of-one-in-northern-england-180989118/</guid></item><item><title>托马斯·杰斐逊的《独立宣言》原始草稿现在可以在国会图书馆看到</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thomas-jeffersons-original-rough-draft-of-the-declaration-of-independence-can-be-seen-at-library-of-congress-180989113/</link><description>新展览展示了该文件的编辑方式，还展出了葛底斯堡演说的早期副本</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thomas-jeffersons-original-rough-draft-of-the-declaration-of-independence-can-be-seen-at-library-of-congress-180989113/</guid></item><item><title>这块霸王龙化石的拍卖价格可能是有史以来拍卖价格最高的恐龙。科学家担心他们会失去研究它的机会</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</link><description>“Gus”的起价为 1900 万美元，这对于公共机构来说是一个很高的价格。私人收藏的标本对于研究人员来说更难检查，而且它们实际上不可能包含在顶级科学期刊的研究中</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 20:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</guid></item><item><title>世界上最大的运营蒸汽机车重达 120 万磅。现在，历史悠久的火车可能会驶向您的城镇</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-largest-operating-steam-locomotive-in-the-world-weighs-1-2-million-pounds-now-the-historic-train-may-be-coming-to-your-town-180989112/</link><description>Big Boy No. 4014 建于 20 世纪 40 年代，在行驶超过 100 万英里后于 1961 年退役。现在它正在全国范围内庆祝美国诞辰 250 周年</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 17:26:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-largest-operating-steam-locomotive-in-the-world-weighs-1-2-million-pounds-now-the-historic-train-may-be-coming-to-your-town-180989112/</guid></item><item><title>世界卫生组织警告称，到 2050 年，癌症病例预计将增加近一倍。低收入国家将受到不成比例的影响</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cancer-cases-are-expected-to-nearly-double-by-2050-warns-the-who-low-income-countries-will-be-disproportionately-affected-180989102/</link><description>世界卫生组织在一份新报告中预测，到 2050 年，每年新增确诊病例将从目前的约 2060 万增加到近 3500 万。增幅最大的地区将是非洲和东地中海地区</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 15:44:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cancer-cases-are-expected-to-nearly-double-by-2050-warns-the-who-low-income-countries-will-be-disproportionately-affected-180989102/</guid></item><item><title>今年北美太平洋沿岸发现近150头灰鲸死亡，科学家敲响了警钟</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nearly-150-gray-whales-have-been-found-dead-along-north-americas-pacific-shore-this-year-prompting-scientists-to-sound-the-alarm-180989109/</link><description>每年沿着西海岸在北极和墨西哥之间迁徙的东部灰鲸的数量近年来一直在下降。环保人士表示，2026 年可能是有记录以来海洋哺乳动物死亡人数最多的一年</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nearly-150-gray-whales-have-been-found-dead-along-north-americas-pacific-shore-this-year-prompting-scientists-to-sound-the-alarm-180989109/</guid></item><item><title>几千年前，两只狼是如何来到这个偏远岛屿的？研究人员认为人类将它们带到那里，然后照顾它们</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-two-wolves-end-up-on-this-remote-island-thousands-of-years-ago-researchers-think-humans-brought-them-there-then-cared-for-them-180989110/</link><description>这一发现表明，在驯养狗出现很久之后，人类可能仍与狼保持着关系</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-two-wolves-end-up-on-this-remote-island-thousands-of-years-ago-researchers-think-humans-brought-them-there-then-cared-for-them-180989110/</guid></item><item><title>参观考古学家在这座埋藏在埃及绿洲中、拥有 1600 年历史的拜占庭基督教小镇中发现的文物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-artifacts-that-archaeologists-discovered-in-this-1600-year-old-byzantine-christian-town-buried-in-an-oasis-in-egypt-180989106/</link><description>这个泥砖村庄拥有街道、塔楼和一座大教堂。研究人员出土了日常用品，如谷物研磨机、烤箱和约 200 个陶片——写在破碎陶器上的古代收据和笔记</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 20:07:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-artifacts-that-archaeologists-discovered-in-this-1600-year-old-byzantine-christian-town-buried-in-an-oasis-in-egypt-180989106/</guid></item><item><title>在美国，可导致腹泻数周的寄生虫感染病例迅速增加，以下是您需要了解的内容</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cases-of-a-parasitic-infection-that-can-cause-diarrhea-for-weeks-are-rapidly-rising-in-the-us-heres-what-to-know-180989108/</link><description>这种疾病是由微小寄生虫卡耶塔环孢子虫引起的，它通过被粪便污染的食物或水传播，通常在农场。卫生官员仍在调查多州疫情的来源</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 19:26:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cases-of-a-parasitic-infection-that-can-cause-diarrhea-for-weeks-are-rapidly-rising-in-the-us-heres-what-to-know-180989108/</guid></item><item><title>在最近的一次无耻抢劫中，价值 500 万美元的珠宝和艺术品从法国著名设计师博物馆被盗</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-latest-brazen-heist-jewelry-and-artworks-worth-5-million-were-stolen-from-famed-french-designer-lalique-museum-180989105/</link><description>三名窃贼从法国东部的莱俪博物馆偷走了 27 件藏品，其中包括一件蜻蜓吊坠</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 17:57:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-latest-brazen-heist-jewelry-and-artworks-worth-5-million-were-stolen-from-famed-french-designer-lalique-museum-180989105/</guid></item><item><title>大黄蜂在吃完甜食后似乎会“舔嘴唇”，在尝到不好的味道时会摇头，暗示了昆虫的内心生活</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-seem-to-lick-their-lips-after-sweet-treats-and-shake-their-heads-at-bad-tastes-hinting-at-the-insects-inner-lives-180989098/</link><description>慢动作视频表明，昆虫在喜欢或不喜欢零食时会表现出不同的行为。这些发现可能提供一种研究他们的情绪状态的新方法</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 15:45:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-seem-to-lick-their-lips-after-sweet-treats-and-shake-their-heads-at-bad-tastes-hinting-at-the-insects-inner-lives-180989098/</guid></item><item><title>大约 10 万年前，这个人脸部被刺伤，但幸存下来。他可能是第一批已知的锋利武器袭击受害者之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/roughly-100000-years-ago-this-man-got-stabbed-in-the-face-and-survived-hes-likely-one-of-the-first-known-victims-of-an-attack-by-a-sharp-weapon-180989103/</link><description>研究人员对卡夫泽洞穴中发现的一具年轻成年男性遗骸进行了调查，称伤势随着时间的推移而愈合，这意味着受害者的社区可能照顾过他</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 13:53:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/roughly-100000-years-ago-this-man-got-stabbed-in-the-face-and-survived-hes-likely-one-of-the-first-known-victims-of-an-attack-by-a-sharp-weapon-180989103/</guid></item><item><title>科学家称，南澳大利亚致命藻华背后的罪魁祸首可能是迄今为止测试过的毒性最强的物种</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-culprit-behind-south-australias-deadly-algal-bloom-might-be-the-most-toxic-species-ever-tested-scientists-say-180989100/</link><description>卡伦藻 (Karenia cristata) 是一种罕见的微小藻类，会产生损害神经细胞的毒素，在极低浓度下即可致命</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 12:46:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-culprit-behind-south-australias-deadly-algal-bloom-might-be-the-most-toxic-species-ever-tested-scientists-say-180989100/</guid></item><item><title>驼鹿是科罗拉多州本地人还是引进的外来者？新研究表明这些动物已经在该州生活了几个世纪</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/are-moose-colorado-natives-or-introduced-outsiders-new-research-suggests-that-the-animals-have-lived-in-the-state-for-centuries-180989091/</link><description>官员们表示，驼鹿直到 20 世纪 70 年代末才被引入该州。但历史文献和考古证据表明，他们早在那之前就居住在那里</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 20:15:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/are-moose-colorado-natives-or-introduced-outsiders-new-research-suggests-that-the-animals-have-lived-in-the-state-for-centuries-180989091/</guid></item><item><title>乡村音乐传奇人物多莉·帕顿的自传音乐剧《探索她从田纳西州东部出发的旅程》将于今年冬天在百老汇上演</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/country-music-legend-dolly-partons-autobiographical-musical-exploring-her-journey-from-east-tennessee-will-hit-broadway-this-winter-180989099/</link><description>《多莉：真正的原创音乐剧》去年在帕顿的家乡纳什维尔首演</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 19:27:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/country-music-legend-dolly-partons-autobiographical-musical-exploring-her-journey-from-east-tennessee-will-hit-broadway-this-winter-180989099/</guid></item></channel></rss>